What you need to know:

The Portuguese made a trio substitution in the 65th minute, roping in Philemon Otieno, John Macharia and Abdoul Karim for Cliffton Miheso, Samuel Onyango and Kelvin Wesonga.Opiyo then saved Rangers, punching out Kenneth Muguna's header as he denied the Kenyan international a clear chance to restore parity.Okumbi brought in former Gor Mahia defender Bernard Ondiek, Cavine Odongo and Steiner Musasia for Joshua Yatini, Alex Lungaji and Nambute respectively in the 77th minute to defend the slim lead.